87/wizz-air-to-serve-brussels-airport-from-summer-2020/|title=Wizz Air to serve Brussels Airport from summer 2020|publisher=brusselstimes.com|date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n===Cargo===\n{{more sources needed|date=December 2019}}\n{{Airport-dest-list\n<!-- -->\n|[[Air Alg\u00e9rie Cargo]] | [[Houari Boumediene Airport|Algiers]], [[Mohammed V International Airport|Casablanca]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Asiana Cargo]] | [[Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport|Anchorage]], [[London\u2013Stansted]], [[New York\u2013JFK]], [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul\u2013Incheon]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[ASL Airlines Belgium]]| [[Helsinki Airport|Helsinki]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Avianca Cargo]]| [[Miami International Airport|Miami]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aircargonews.net/news/airport/single-view/news/avianca-cargo-adds-brussels-freighter-flights.html|title=Avianca Cargo adds Brussels freighter flights|work=aircargonews.net|access-date=28 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129101559/https://www.aircargonews.net/news/airport/single-view/news/avianca-cargo-adds-brussels-freighter-flights.html|archive-date=29 November 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[DHL Aviation]]| [[Bahrain International Airport|Bahrain]], [[Barcelona\u2013El Prat Airport|Barcelona]], [[Orio al Serio Airport|Bergamo]], [[M. R. \u0160tef\u00e1nik Airport|Bratislava]], [[Budapest Ferenc Liszt International Airport|Budapest]], [[Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport|Cincinnati]], [[Copenhagen Airport|Copenhagen]], [[East Midlands Airport|East Midlands]], [[Gardermoen Airport|Oslo\u2013Gardermoen]], [[Helsinki-Vantaa Airport|Helsinki]], [[Murtala Muhammed International Airport|Lagos]], [[Leipzig/Halle Airport|Leipzig/Halle]], [[Lisbon Portela Airport|Lisbon]], [[London\u2013Heathrow]], [[Madrid Barajas Airport|Madrid]], [[Shanghai Pudong International Airport|Shanghai]], [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul\u2013Incheon]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aviation24.be/airlines/atlas-air/atlas-air-operate-dhl-flights-boeing-747-400f-brussels-airport/|title=Atlas Air to operate flights for DHL from Brussels Airport by boeing 747-400F|work=Aviation24.be}}</ref> [[Vitoria Airport|Vitoria]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Emirates SkyCargo]] | [[O'Hare International Airport|Chicago\u2013O'Hare]], [[Al Maktoum International Airport|Dubai\u2013Al Maktoum]], [[Rickenbacker International Airport|Lockbourne]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Ethiopian Airlines Cargo]] | [[Bole International Airport|Addis Ababa]], [[Al Maktoum International Airport|Dubai\u2013Al Maktoum]], [[Guangzhou Baiyun International Airport|Guangzhou]], [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]], [[New York\u2013JFK]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[Shanghai Pudong International Airport|Shanghai]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aviation24.be/airlines/ethiopian-airlines/ethiopian-airlines-cargo-relaunches-cargo-flights-brussels-airport-26-march/|title=Ethiopian Airlines Cargo relaunches cargo flights at Brussels Airport from 26 March|work=Aviation24.be}}</ref>,  [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul-Incheon]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[LATAM Cargo Chile]] | [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]], [[Viracopos\u2013Campinas International Airport|Campinas\u2013Viracopos]], [[Comodoro Arturo Merino Ben\u00edtez International Airport|Santiago de Chile]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aviation24.be/airlines/latam/latam-cargo-chile/moves-away-two-weekly-flights-from-amsterdam-schiphol-to-brussels-airport/|title= LATAM Cargo chile moves away two weekly flights from amsterdam schiphol to brussels airport|work=Aviation24.be}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Qatar Airways Cargo]] | [[Accra Airport|Accra]],<ref name=\"qrcargo.com\"/> [[Hamad International Airport|Doha]]<ref name=\"qrcargo.com\">[http://www.qrcargo.com/docs/07.Summer%2019%20Freighter%20Schedule%20Issue%207%20-%20Effective%201st%20October%202019%20to%2026th%20October%202019.pdf qrcargo.com] retrieved 12 September 2019</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Royal Air Maroc]] | [[Mohammed V Int