y couldn't operate more cargo flights at night because of noise for the people living in the surrounding area.\n* The 2016 decrease in passenger numbers and aircraft movements results from the [[2016 Brussels bombings]] which caused the airport to close for 11 days before reopening with severely reduced capacity.\n\n===Routes===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%\" width= align=\n|+ Busiest European routes from Brussels Airport<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.brusselsairport.be/uploads/media/default/0001/16/57f01fd3429acd1ae5e79f43cf99634cd3b73d58.pdf# |title=Archived copy |access-date=27 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627202745/https://www.brusselsairport.be/uploads/media/default/0001/16/57f01fd3429acd1ae5e79f43cf99634cd3b73d58.pdf# |archive-date=27 June 2018 |url-status=dead  }}</ref><ref name=\"issuu.com\">https://issuu.com/brusselsairport/docs/brutrends_2018/1?ff</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Destination\n! Airport(s)\n! Passengers 2018\n! Passengers 2017\n! Passengers 2016\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Madrid]]\n| [[Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|MAD]]\n| 1,009,602\n| 966,146\n| 763,016\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Barcelona]]\n| [[Barcelona El Prat Airport|BCN]]\n| 940,782\n| 927,618\n| 889,180\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Lisbon]]\n| [[Lisbon Portela Airport|LIS]]\n| 733,920\n| 738,243\n| 698,131\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Rome]]\n| [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|FCO]]\n| 720,067\n| 719,436\n| 713,392\n|- \n| 5\n| [[London]]\n| [[London Heathrow Airport|LHR]]\n| 688,333\n| 654,712\n| 587,487\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Milan]]\n| [[Malpensa Airport|MXP]], [[Linate Airport|LIN]]\n| 639,346\n| 644,841\n| 492,068\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Geneva]]\n| [[Geneva International Airport|GVA]]\n| 608,377\n| 591,857\n| 545,230\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Frankfurt]]\n| [[Frankfurt International Airport|FRA]]\n| 589,109\n| 549,296\n| 467,068\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Malaga]]\n| [[M\u00e1laga Airport|AGP]]\n| 537,230\n| 533,863\n| 499,228\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Berlin]]\n| [[Berlin Tegel Airport|TXL]], [[Berlin Sch\u00f6nefeld Airport|SXF]]\n| 497,362