{"title_page": "100 (2019 film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Indian Tamil-language action film written and directed by Sam Anton}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = 100\n| image          = Poster of 100.jpg\n| caption        = \n| film name      = \n| director       = [[Sam Anton]]\n| producer       = Kaviya Mahesh\n| writer         = Sam Anton\n| based on       = \n| starring       = [[Atharvaa]]<br />[[Hansika Motwani]]<br />[[Radha Ravi]]<br />Raaj Aiyyappa\n| music          = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cinematography = Krishnan Vasant\n| editing        = [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]\n| studio         = Auraa Cinemas\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|2019|5|9}}\n| runtime        = 141 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n}}\n'''''100''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film]] written and directed by [[Sam Anton]] in his third directorial venture. The film features [[Atharvaa]] and [[Hansika Motwani]] in the lead roles, while [[Radha Ravi]] and [[Yogi Babu]] play supporting roles. The music was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], with editing done by [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]] and cinematography by Krishnan Vasant. The film began production during December 2017 and completed its shoot by August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/atharvaa-hansika-romantic-comedy-starts-rolling-imagegallery-kollywood-rmpo6Hhfabgbe.html|title=Atharvaa-Hansika romantic comedy starts rolling!|website=Sify.com|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref> It was released on 9 May 2019 to mixed to positive reviews from the audience as well as critics and become an above average success.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/100-review-a-watchable-cop-action-entertainer-review-tamil-tfkjpCebjehdb.html</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nSathya ([[Atharvaa]]) wants to be an upright cop hoping that his life will become adventurous by chasing criminals and solving mysteries, but due to his bad luck, he gets posted in a control room as an emergency call operator. Initially, Sathya thinks that his job is just as mundane as his girlfriend Nisha ([[Hansika Motwani]]) who works in a call center. However, one call which he misses involved the life of a small boy who was kidnapped. Sathya nabs the criminals behind the kidnapping, but soon the 100th emergency call that he receives will be the one which will turn his life upside-down. Sathya comes to know that a young girl who was declared dead is alive and has been kidnapped and kept by a criminal. How Sathya converts his mundane control room atmosphere into an adventurous ride and unmasks the criminals behind the series of missing young girls, forms the crux of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Atharvaa]] as Sub-Inspector Sathya\n*[[Hansika Motwani]] as Nisha\n*[[Radha Ravi]] as Pistol Perumal\n*Raaj Aiyyappa as Vicky (Vignesh), Nisha's brother\n*[[Yogi Babu]] as   SI Jackson \n*[[Saravanan (actor)|Saravanan]] as Ganesh, Sathya's father\n*[[Nirosha]] as Sathya's mother\n*[[Cheenu Mohan]] as David\n*[[Aadukalam Naren]] as Police Commissioner\n*[[Mahanadi Shankar]] as Inspector Murugesan\n*Pasanga Sivakumar as Anwar's father\n*[[Mime Gopi]] as Daas\n*[[Swaminathan]] as Gajapathy Swamy alias Gary\n*Mahesh as Anwar\n*''Eruma Saani'' Harija as Ayesha\n*''Eruma Saani'' Vijay as Sathya's friend\n*Sampath Ram as Inspector Jegadeesh\n*Kadhal Kannan as Victim's father\n*Vijay Varadharaj as Caller\n*Praneshvar as Hari Krishnan\n*Pillayar Ruthru as Rajesh\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nIn June 2017, producer [[S. Michael Rayappan]] of Global Infotainment announced that he would work together on a project with actor [[Atharvaa]], which would be directed by Sam Anton.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/news/atharvaa-teams-sam-anton-new-film/|title=Atharvaa Teams Up With Sam Anton For New Film|date=14 June 2017|website=Silverscren.in|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref> However, the failure of Rayappan's ''[[Anbanavan Asaradhavan Adangadhavan]]'' put him in a financially difficult position, and he subsequently withdrew from the project. In a turn of events, production house Auraa Cinemas took over the project, with [[Hansika Motwani]] joining the team to play the lead actress in December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/hansika-to-romance-atharvaa-in-sam-anton-film-news-tamil-rmhp5Jegfbdaf.html|title=Hansika to romance Atharvaa in Sam Anton film|website=Sify.com|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nPortraying a police officer for the first time, Atharvaa underwent stunt training for the role. Tamil YouTube personalities Vijay and Harija also worked on the film, as did [[Radharavi]], [[Mime Gopi]] and [[Yogi Babu]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/atharvaa-goes-after-smugglers-in-100/articleshow/65413665.cms|title=Atharvaa goes after smugglers in '100'|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref> The film's shoot was completed in July 2018, with the team announcing that only one further song sequence was left to be shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/photo-atharvaa-wraps-up-his-upcoming-film-100/articleshow/64973640.cms|title=Photo: Atharvaa wraps up his upcoming film \u2018100\u2019|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n==Box office==\nThe movie got very less occupancy on its first weekend. Due to positive word of mouth,it was a '''decent hit''' at the box office and completed its 50 days of theatrical run.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], collaborating with the director for the first time. All lyrics are written by [[Madhan Karky]], and the audio rights are secured by [[Sa Re Ga Ma]].\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = 100\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 9:06\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sa Re Ga Ma]]\n| producer     = Sam C. S.\n| prev_title   = [[NOTA (film)|NOTA]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = [[Ayogya (2019 film)|Ayogya]]\n| next_year    = 2019\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Agulu Bagulu\n| lyrics1 = Logan\n| extra1 = [[Arjun Chandy]]\n| length1 = 4:26\n| title2 = Ye di Raasathi\n| lyrics2 = Kavita Thomas\n| extra2 = Sathyaprakash\n| length2 = 4:38\n| title3 = Nanba\n| lyrics3 = Sam. C. S\n| extra3 = Sam. C. S\n| length3 = 3:02\n| total_length: 9:06\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8458736}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n\n\n{{2010s-Tamil-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Indian Tamil-language action film written and directed by Sam Anton}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = 100\n| image          = Poster of 100.jpg\n| caption        = \n| film name      = \n| director       = [[Sam Anton]]\n| producer       = Kaviya Mahesh\n| writer         = Sam Anton\n| based on       = \n| starring       = [[Atharvaa]]<br />[[Hansika Motwani]]<br />[[Radha Ravi]]<br />Raaj Aiyyappa\n| music          = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cinematography = Krishnan Vasant\n| editing        = [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]\n| studio         = Auraa Cinemas\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|2019|5|9}}\n| runtime        = 141 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n}}\n'''''100''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film]] written and directed by [[Sam Anton]] in his third directorial venture. The film features [[Atharvaa]] and [[Hansika Motwani]] in the lead roles, while [[Radha Ravi]] and [[Yogi Babu]] play supporting roles. The music was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], with editing done by [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]] and cinematography by Krishnan Vasant. The film began production during December 2017 and completed its shoot by August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/atharvaa-hansika-romantic-comedy-starts-rolling-imagegallery-kollywood-rmpo6Hhfabgbe.html|title=Atharvaa-Hansika romantic comedy starts rolling!|website=Sify.com|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref> It was released on 9 May 2019 to mixed to positive reviews from the audience as well as critics and become an above average success.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/100-review-a-watchable-cop-action-entertainer-review-tamil-tfkjpCebjehdb.html</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nSathya ([[Atharvaa]]) wants to be an upright cop hoping that his life will become adventurous by chasing criminals and solving mysteries, but due to his bad luck, he gets posted in a control room as an emergency call operator. Initially, Sathya thinks that his job is just as mundane as his girlfriend Nisha ([[Hansika Motwani]]) who works in an call center. However, that one call which he misses involved the life of a kidnapped small boy. Sathya nabs the criminals behind the kidnapping, but soon the 100th emergency call that he receives will be the one which turns his life upside-down. Sathya comes to know that a young girl who was declared dead is alive and has been kidnapped and kept by a criminal. How Sathya converts his mundane control room atmosphere into an adventurous ride and unmasks the criminals behind the series of missing young girls, forms the crux of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Atharvaa]] as Sub-Inspector Sathya\n*[[Hansika Motwani]] as Nisha\n*[[Radha Ravi]] as Pistol Perumal\n*Raaj Aiyyappa as Vicky (Vignesh), Nisha's brother\n*[[Yogi Babu]] as   SI Jackson \n*[[Saravanan (actor)|Saravanan]] as Ganesh, Sathya's father\n*[[Nirosha]] as Sathya's mother\n*[[Cheenu Mohan]] as David\n*[[Aadukalam Naren]] as Police Commissioner\n*[[Mahanadi Shankar]] as Inspector Murugesan\n*Pasanga Sivakumar as Anwar's father\n*[[Mime Gopi]] as Daas\n*[[Swaminathan]] as Gajapathy Swamy alias Gary\n*Mahesh as Anwar\n*''Eruma Saani'' Harija as Ayesha\n*''Eruma Saani'' Vijay as Sathya's friend\n*Sampath Ram as Inspector Jegadeesh\n*Kadhal Kannan as Victim's father\n*Vijay Varadharaj as Caller\n*Praneshvar as Hari Krishnan\n*Pillayar Ruthru as Rajesh\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nIn June 2017, producer [[S. Michael Rayappan]] of Global Infotainment announced that he would work together on a project with actor [[Atharvaa]], which would be directed by Sam Anton.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/news/atharvaa-teams-sam-anton-new-film/|title=Atharvaa Teams Up With Sam Anton For New Film|date=14 June 2017|website=Silverscren.in|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref> However, the failure of Rayappan's ''[[Anbanavan Asaradhavan Adangadhavan]]'' put him in a financially difficult position, and he subsequently withdrew from the project. In a turn of events, production house Auraa Cinemas took over the project, with [[Hansika Motwani]] joining the team to play the lead actress in December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/hansika-to-romance-atharvaa-in-sam-anton-film-news-tamil-rmhp5Jegfbdaf.html|title=Hansika to romance Atharvaa in Sam Anton film|website=Sify.com|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nPortraying a police officer for the first time, Atharvaa underwent stunt training for the role. Tamil YouTube personalities Vijay and Harija also worked on the film, as did [[Radharavi]], [[Mime Gopi]] and [[Yogi Babu]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/atharvaa-goes-after-smugglers-in-100/articleshow/65413665.cms|title=Atharvaa goes after smugglers in '100'|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref> The film's shoot was completed in July 2018, with the team announcing that only one further song sequence was left to be shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/photo-atharvaa-wraps-up-his-upcoming-film-100/articleshow/64973640.cms|title=Photo: Atharvaa wraps up his upcoming film \u2018100\u2019|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n==Box office==\nThe movie got very less occupancy on its first weekend. Due to positive word of mouth,it was a '''decent hit''' at the box office and completed its 50 days of theatrical run.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], collaborating with the director for the first time. All lyrics are written by [[Madhan Karky]], and the audio rights are secured by [[Sa Re Ga Ma]].\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = 100\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 9:06\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sa Re Ga Ma]]\n| producer     = Sam C. S.\n| prev_title   = [[NOTA (film)|NOTA]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = [[Ayogya (2019 film)|Ayogya]]\n| next_year    = 2019\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Agulu Bagulu\n| lyrics1 = Logan\n| extra1 = [[Arjun Chandy]]\n| length1 = 4:26\n| title2 = Ye di Raasathi\n| lyrics2 = Kavita Thomas\n| extra2 = Sathyaprakash\n| length2 = 4:38\n| title3 = Nanba\n| lyrics3 = Sam. C. S\n| extra3 = Sam. C. S\n| length3 = 3:02\n| total_length: 9:06\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8458736}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n\n\n{{2010s-Tamil-fi