n Capel|rookie=y|WR}}\n{{NFLplayer|&nbsp;5|Dave Klemic|rookie=y|WR}}\n{{NFLplayer|&nbsp;9|J. J. Moses|rookie=y|WR}}\n}}\n\n==Schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Week\n! Date\n! Opponent\n! Result\n! Network\n! TV Time (CT)\n! Attendance\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 1\n| September 9, 2001\n| [[2001 Oakland Raiders season|Oakland Raiders]]\n| L 27\u201324\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>78,844</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 2\n| September 23, 2001\n| [[2001 New York Giants season|New York Giants]]\n| L 13\u20133\n| FOX\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>77,666</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 3\n| September 30, 2001\n| at [[2001 Washington Redskins season|Washington Redskins]]\n| W 45\u201313\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>76,573</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 4\n| October 7, 2001\n| at [[2001 Denver Broncos season|Denver Broncos]]\n| L 20\u20136\n| CBS\n| 3:15PM\n| <center>75,037</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 5\n| October 14, 2001\n| [[2001 Pittsburgh Steelers season|Pittsburgh Steelers]]\n| L 20\u201317\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>78,413</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 6\n| October 21, 2001\n| at [[2001 Arizona Cardinals season|Arizona Cardinals]]\n| L 24\u201316\n| CBS\n| 3:05PM\n| <center>35,916</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 7\n| October 25, 2001\n| [[2001 Indianapolis Colts season|Indianapolis Colts]]\n| L 35\u201328\n| ESPN\n| 7:30PM\n| <center>74,212</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 8\n| November 4, 2001\n| at [[2001 San Diego Chargers season|San Diego Chargers]]\n| W 25\u201320\n| CBS\n| 3:05PM\n| <center>58,789</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 9\n| November 11, 2001\n| at [[2001 New York Jets season|New York Jets]]\n| L 27\u20137\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>78,234</center>\n|-\n| 10\n| colspan=6 align=\"center\" | ''Bye''\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 11\n| November 25, 2001\n| [[2001 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle Seahawks]]\n| W 19\u20137\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>77,357</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 12\n| November 29, 2001\n| [[2001 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia Eagles]]\n| L 23\u201310\n| ESPN\n| 7:30PM\n| <center>77,087</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 13\n| December 9, 2001\n| at [[2001 Oakland Raiders season|Oakland Raiders]]\n| L 28\u201326\n| CBS\n| 3:15PM\n| <center>60,784</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 14\n| December 16, 2001\n| [[2001 Denver Broncos season|Denver Broncos]]\n| W 26\u201323\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>77,778</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 15\n| December 23, 2001\n| [[2001 San Diego Chargers season|San Diego Chargers]]\n| W 20\u201317\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>76,131</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 16\n| December 30, 2001\n| at [[2001 Jacksonville Jaguars season|Jacksonville Jaguars]]\n| W 30\u201326\n| CBS\n| 12:00PM\n| <center>59,396</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 17\n| January 6, 2002*\n| at [[2001 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle Seahawks]]\n| L 21\u201318\n| CBS\n| 3:05PM\n| <center>58,460</center>\n|}\n\n<small>*Game originally scheduled for September 16, but was postponed along with all Week 2 games following the [[September 11 Terrorist Attacks]]</small>\n\n==Standings==\n{{2001 AFC West standings}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Kansas City Chiefs}}\n{{Kansas City Chiefs seasons}}\n{{2001 NFL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2001 Kansas City Chiefs Season}}\n[[Category:2001 National Football League season by team|Kansas City Chiefs]]\n[[Category:Kansas City Chiefs seasons]]\n[[Category:2001 in sports in Missouri|Kansas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox NFL_season\n| team = Kansas City Chiefs\n| year = 2001\n| record = 6\u201310\n| division_place = 4th [[AFC West]]\n| coach = [[Dick Vermeil]]\n| stadium = [[Arrowhead Stadium]]\n| playoffs = ''did not qualify''\n| pro bowlers = RB Priest Holmes<br>TE Tony Gonzalez<br>G Will Shields\n| shortnavlink    = Chiefs seasons\n}}\n\nThe '''{{nfly|2001}} [[Kansas City Chiefs]] [[List of Kansas City Chiefs seasons|season]]''' was the franchise's 32nd season in the [[National Football League]], the 42nd overall and the first under head coach Dick Vermeil, and failing to qualify for the playoffs or to improve upon their 7\u20139 record from 2000, with a 6\u201310 record, which netted them a fourth place finish in the [[AFC West]].  \n\nAlong with new coaches joining the team, new additions appeared on the Chiefs\u2019 roster, including [[running back]] [[Priest Holmes]] and [[quarterback]] [[Trent Green]]. Coach [[Dick Vermeil]] began to install a powerful offense similar to the [[Greatest Show on Turf|one he installed]] in [[1999 St. Louis Rams season|St. Louis]] to win [[Super Bowl XXXIV]].\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===NFL draft===\n{{main article|2001 NFL draft}}\n{{NFL team draft start\n | year     = 2001\n | teamname = Kansas City Chiefs\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 3\n | pick       = 75\n | player     = [[Eric Downing]]\n | position   = [[Defensive Tackle]]\n | college    = [[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft end\n | hof = no\n}}\n\n===Undrafted free agents===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ 2001 Undrafted Free Agents of note\n!Player\n!Position\n!College\n|-\n|[[Ian Allen (gridiron football)|Ian Allen]]\n|Tackle\n|[[Purdue Boilermakers football|Purdue]]\n|}\n\n==Personnel==\n===Staff===\n{{NFL final staff\n| year = 2001\n| team = Kansas City Chiefs\n\n| front_office =\n* Founder \u2013 [[Lamar Hunt]]\n* President/General Manager/Chief Executive Officer \u2013 [[Carl Peterson]]\n* Chairman of the Board \u2013 [[Jack Steadman]]\n* Executive Vice President/Assistant General Manager \u2013 Dennis Thum\n* Vice President of Football Operations/Player Personnel \u2013 [[Lynn Stiles]]\n* Director of Football Administration \u2013 [[Mike White (American football coach)|Mike White]]\n*