id, M.C. Macrophage-secreted granulin supports pancreatic cancer metastasis by inducing liver fibrosis. (2016) ''Nature Cell Biology.'' 18(5):549-60. DOI: 10.1038/ncb3340<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nielsen|first=Sebastian R.|last2=Quaranta|first2=Valeria|last3=Linford|first3=Andrea|last4=Emeagi|first4=Perpetua|last5=Rainer|first5=Carolyn|last6=Santos|first6=Almudena|last7=Ireland|first7=Lucy|last8=Sakai|first8=Takao|last9=Sakai|first9=Keiko|last10=Kim|first10=Yong-Sam|last11=Engle|first11=Dannielle|date=05 2016|title=Macrophage-secreted granulin supports pancreatic cancer metastasis by inducing liver fibrosis|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27088855|journal=Nature Cell Biology|volume=18|issue=5|pages=549\u2013560|doi=10.1038/ncb3340|issn=1476-4679|pmc=4894551|pmid=27088855}}</ref>\n* Seifert, L., Werba, G., Tiwari, S., Giao Ly, N.N., Alothman, S., Alqunaibit, D., Avanzi, A., Barilla, R., Daley, D., Greco, S.H., Torres-Hernandez, A., Pergamo, M., Ochi, A., Zambirinis, C.P., Pansari, M., Rendon, M., Tippens, D., Hundeyin, M., Mani, V.R., Hajdu, C., Engle, D., Miller, G. The necrosome promotes pancreatic oncogenesis via CXCL1 and Mincle-induced immune suppression. (2016) ''Nature.'' 532(7598):245-9. DOI: 10.1038/nature17403<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Seifert|first=Lena|last2=Werba|first2=Gregor|last3=Tiwari|first3=Shaun|last4=Giao Ly|first4=Nancy Ngoc|last5=Alothman|first5=Sara|last6=Alqunaibit|first6=Dalia|last7=Avanzi|first7=Antonina|last8=Barilla|first8=Rocky|last9=Daley|first9=Donnele|last10=Greco|first10=Stephanie H.|last11=Torres-Hernandez|first11=Alejandro|date=2016-04-14|title=The necrosome promotes pancreatic oncogenesis via CXCL1 and Mincle-induced immune suppression|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27049944|journal=Nature|volume=532|issue=7598|pages=245\u2013249|doi=10.1038/nature17403|issn=1476-4687|pmc=4833566|pmid=27049944}}</ref>\n* Boj, S.F., Hwang, C.I., Baker, L.A., Engle, D.D., Tuveson, D.A., Clevers, H. Model organoids provide new research 